        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 26 at 12:00AM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 1200 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles north of Wolford, or 19 miles northeast of Rugby, moving
northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wolford, Mylo, Agate, and Nanson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for
north central North Dakota.</instruction>
